The LPAT is a demanding but fair test reflecting the tasks of a programmer or analyst.
The LPAT is a test that measures a job applicant's potential rather than his/her knowledge of a specific computer language.  It helps you compare your applicants with each other and with national norms.
The LPAT provides accurate, quantified, systematic information about your candidatesÂ’ mental abilities, going beyond what resumes, GPAs and interviews can tell you.
Upon completion of the test, a score report is produced with an overall score and with sub-scores. 
For more information on the Language-Free Programmer/Analyst Test see:
http://aprtestingservices.com/business/LPAT10.htm
